Project Title
StudySmart, Student Task and Deadline Manager

Problem Statement
College students miss deadlines, quizzes, and project submissions.
Many students depend on memory or scattered notes.
This leads to cramming, stress, and missed requirements.
Students need one organized system for academic tasks.

Proposed Solution
The team will build a Task and Deadline Manager application.
The application will let students:
- Add subjects and tasks
- Set deadlines
- View pending and completed tasks
- Receive reminders
- Track task status

The system will save data in a local file or a database.

Target Users
- College students
- Senior high school students
- Working students
- People who manage academic tasks

Core Features
Add Task
- Task name
- Subject
- Deadline
- Priority level

View Tasks
- Show pending tasks
- Show completed tasks

Task Actions
- Mark task as completed
- Delete task
- Search by subject
- Search by deadline

Tools and Technologies
Option 1
- Python
- File handling with TXT or JSON
- OOP principles

Option 2
- Python with Tkinter GUI
- SQLite database

System Flow
1. Start
- The app opens.
- The app checks SQLite or local JSON/TXT storage.
- The app loads existing tasks into the main view.

2. Input
- The user selects Add Task.
- The app asks for task name, subject, deadline, and priority.

3. Validation and Save
- The app checks empty fields.
- The app checks date format.
- The app saves valid data.

4. Display and Filter
- The main view refreshes after save.
- The user searches by subject or date.
- The app filters records.

5. Status Update
- The user marks a task as completed.
- The app updates the completed value.
- The app refreshes the view.

6. Exit
- The app closes the storage connection safely.

Data Model
- Task name, subject, priority: String
- Deadline: Date in YYYY-MM-DD
- Completed status: Boolean stored as 0 or 1
- Task ID: Auto increment integer

Expected Challenges
- Date formatting and validation
- Reliable data persistence during unexpected closure
- GUI refresh after add, update, or delete
- Input error handling for invalid text or symbols

Optional Features
- Reminder alert for tasks due within 24 hours
- Priority color coding, red high, yellow medium, green low
- Dark mode toggle
- Status pie chart, completed versus pending

Development Timeline
Week 1: Planning and design
Week 2: Development and testing
Week 3: Finalization and submission

